main event: Two objects were tracked on radar at an altitude of 40-50,000 feet near Portsmouth, New Hampshire on October 26, 1963, with one confirmed by other radar stations and the other disappearing.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 10-12 minutes., The first object was confirmed by multiple radar stations., The second object disappeared from radar without any visual confirmation., There were multiple possible conclusions including aircraft, satellite, or missile., No photographs were taken or included in the report.
